<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2015/03/16/getting-started-with-couchbase-and-spring-data-couchbase">Getting Started with Couchbase and Spring Data Couchbase</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/engineering">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/fb22593caf24e4bb4c98d467cdd247e6?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/jlong">Josh Long</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2015-03-16 05:20:06.552">March 16, 2015</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="2022" href="/blog/2015/03/16/getting-started-with-couchbase-and-spring-data-couchbase#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><blockquote>
<p>This blog was inspired by a talk that <a href="https://twitter.com/ldoguin">Laurent Doguin</a>, a developer advocate over at Couchbase, and I gave at <a href="http://www.couchbase.com/connect/">Couchbase Connect</a> last year. Merci Laurent!</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is a demo of the <a href="https://github.com/spring-projects/spring-data-couchbase">Spring Data Couchbase</a> integration. From <a href="https://spring.io/projects/spring-data-couchbase">the project page</a>, Spring Data Couchbase is:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Spring Data Couchbase project provides integration with the Couchbase Server database. Key functional areas of Spring Data Couchbase are a POJO centric model for interacting with Couchbase Buckets and easily writing a Repository style data access layer.</p>
</blockquote>
</div>
</section>
